Volgograd Governor and Governor of West Kazakhstan region have signed the cooperation agreement.
On September 16 in Sochi was opened the XII Forum of interregional cooperation of Russia and Kazakhstan.
A key topic was cooperation in the sphere of agro-industrial complex and ensuring food security.
In the international forum is attended by the Governor of the Volgograd region Andrei Bocharov.
Note that Kazakhstan is one of the strategic partners of our region.
Annually increasing economic cooperation and strengthening cultural ties.
September 16, Andrey Bocharov and akim of West Kazakhstan region Nurlan Nogayev has signed a cooperation agreement.
The document will allow to create favorable conditions for mutual supplies of goods, as well as to increase interaction of the industrial enterprises.
Ended Russian-Belarusian military exercises "Union Shield 2015".
The West country ended with a joint Russian-Belarusian military exercises "Union Shield 2015", reports "Russia 24".
Maneuvers were held in landfills in the Leningrad, Pskov and Kaliningrad regions, as well as in the Baltic sea.
Was attended by over eight thousand servicemen and about four hundred pieces of equipment.
On the last day of the exercises the ships of the Baltic fleet worked artillery strike at surface and shore targets, as well as the reflection of air attack imaginary enemy.
Where can I leave feedback on the work of the usher in Murmansk?
In Management of Federal bailiff service of the Murmansk region reported that in order to improve the protection of the rights and legitimate interests of citizens and organizations in the Agency has a book of reviews and suggestions.
In it, the citizens can leave a message about the quality of work of court bailiffs and other officials of the administration, information on the deficiencies in the work, and also to Express their suggestions and comments.
In the management a copy of the book of comments and suggestions is located in the Central hall, in a special pocket in a prominent and accessible place at the checkpoint in the building.
In the structural units of the office the book is in the office.
Given the nature of the feedback or suggestions in necessary cases, the initiator shall send a written answer.
XI XI's calls to make the economy more open to the world
The economy should become more open to the world to spur its growth, said Tuesday the President XI XI Jinping in his address to the group, which is tasked to guide the reforms.
"China should concentrate on attracting foreign investors and experts and to develop a policy of openness," said he, addressing the participants of 16th meeting of the Committee of the Central leading group for comprehensive deepening of reforms.
According to him, widening openness and deepening of reforms will give the economy new impetus and vitality and provide a new space for economic development.
The leading group adopted a number of directives, including the introduction of regulation of the access of investors to the market, change the rules of border controls, promoting state-owned enterprises (SOEs), attracting private capital and the revision of the system of registration of inhabitants.
According to the statement, will make the list of sectors of the economy and production, not available for investment.
The system will be gradually to test through trial applications.
This is an important step because it will give the market a greater role in the allocation of resources, the rule of law in the business sphere and increasing openness, according to the statement.
The government will also weaken control over the powers granted to them companies, ensuring that companies will conduct their business.
The statement also said that China will allow border regions to develop new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to enhance local growth.
More spheres will be available to private investors with the aim of increasing the transparency of state-controlled sectors of the economy.
"The government will not change its policy towards foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of companies with foreign financing, and to provide them the best conditions", - said in a statement.
Additionally facilitate the procedure of applying for a permanent residence permit for foreigners, or "green cards", by optimizing the requirements and simplify the process of filing.
The meeting also discussed ensuring the rights of advocates and training professional judges and prosecutors.
According to released after the meeting, the official report, it was also attended by Prime Minister Li Keqiang, and Ministers of unisan Liu and Zhang gaoli.
